-- Work Starts on Sahara Mining’s Mali Steel Plant, Essor Reports
-- B y   D i a k a r i d i a   D e m b e l e
-- 2011-12-28T11:52:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/work-starts-on-sahara-mining-s-mali-steel-plant-essor-reports.html
Sahara Mining SA, an iron-ore
explorer that operates in  Mali , has started construction on a
plant to process steel, l’Essor reported, citing a ceremony with
President Amadou Toumani Toure.  Sandeep Energy & Steel, which includes a 70-megawatt,
thermal power plant, will be in operation by 2013, the Bamako-
based, state-owned newspaper reported. The factory’s cost is
seen at 150 billion CFA francs, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Diakaridia Dembele in Bamako at 
 ddembele@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
